{"overview":"This ternary piece in G-flat major is defined by an atmosphere of intimate, meditative lyricism anchored in a gentle arpeggiated-bass primary theme, with its most distinctive feature being a bold excursion through enharmonic regions in the middle section — pivoting from C-flat major through a German augmented sixth to a phantom E minor/B minor tonal area before dissolving back into the home key. The recapitulation's chromatic-mediant episode and ppp morendo coda further underscore a language of expressive harmonic ambiguity, where enharmonic reinterpretation serves as the piece's central structural and coloristic device.","cross_piece_tags":["ternary","enharmonic_modulation","chromatic_mediant","modal_mixture","arpeggiated_bass","lyrical","meditative","melancholic"]}
